data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer accepts expression trees

The setter parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The entire expression-tree machinery is no longer needed.

---

### 2. Complex type columns — two changes

**a) Duplicate names are now uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column; now they get `Street` and `Street1`. To keep the old names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
    p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
    p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **If you have existing migrations**, these changes will generate schema-altering migrations. Pin column names or plan a migration accordingly.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains potentially-redacted SQL for logging). Add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (redacted constants)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update all method overrides on the interface — `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc. all have the same addition.
